<?xml version='1.0' encoding='utf-8'?>

<!-- ====================================================================== 
   El calentamiento es un <exploration> (distinto a las otras actividades)
   Para RRRRR usar el estilo del calentamiento. Por ejemplo, usar 
   RRRRRR=observa con los "Observa y Pregúntate"
===========================================================================  -->
<exploration xml:id="warm-conteoGrupal-medios" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"> 

<title>Conteo grupal: Medios</title>

<statement>
  <p>Cuenten de <m>\frac{1}{2}</m> en <m>\frac{1}{2}</m>, empezando en <m>\frac{1}{2}</m>.</p>
</statement>

<solution>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>Sample responses:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>The denominator of the fraction never changes.</li>
      <li>The numerator of the fraction is increasing by 1.</li>
      <li>Each row ends with a number you say when you count by 2.</li>
    </ul>
  </solution>


<!-- ============================================================== 
   Notas profesor <prelude> (se pueden mostrar previo al enunciado)                      
===================================================================  -->
<prelude component="profesor"> 

  <!-- Estándares CCSS asociados -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="ccss-actividad-titulo"/></title> 
    <ul>
      <li> 
        <custom ref="ccss-addressing"/>
        <xref ref="ccss-3-NF-A-3-b" text="custom">3.NF.A.3.b</xref>
      </li>
      <li>
        <custom ref="ccss-buildingTowards"/>
        <xref ref="ccss-3-NF-A-2" text="custom">3.NF.A.2</xref>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Tiempo recomendado -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="recommended-time-titulo"/></title>
    <p>10 minutos</p>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Introducción de la actividad -->  
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="narrative-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>The purpose of this Choral Count is to invite students to practice counting by <m>\frac{1}{2}</m> and notice patterns in the count. These understandings help students develop fluency and will be helpful later in this lesson when students recognize and generate equivalent fractions. In the synthesis, students have the opportunity to notice that <m>\frac{2}{2}</m> and <m>\frac{4}{4}</m> are both equal to 1 whole.</p>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Launch -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="launch-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <q>Cuenten de <m>\frac{1}{2}</m> en <m>\frac{1}{2}</m>, empezando en <m>\frac{1}{2}</m></q>
      </li>
      <li>Record as students count. Record 2 fractions in each row, then start a new row. There will be 4 rows.</li>
      <li>Stop counting and recording at <m>\frac{8}{2}</m>.</li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Instrucciones para el desarrollo de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="instructions-teacher-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <q>¿Qué patrones ven?</q>
      </li>
      <li>1–2 minutes: quiet think time</li>
      <li>Record responses.</li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>

</prelude>


<!-- ============================================================== 
   Notas profesor <postlude> (se pueden mostrar después del enunciado)                      
===================================================================  -->
<postlude component="profesor">

  <!-- Síntesis de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="synthesis-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Display count by <m>\frac{1}{4}</m> from the previous lesson. There should be 4 rows and 4 fractions in each row with the count ending at <m>\frac{16}{4}</m>.</li>
      <li>
        <q>¿En qué se parecen estos dos conteos? ¿En qué son diferentes?</q>  (The denominator stays the same in both counts—4 for the last count, and 2 for today’s count. The numerators change in the same way because they both count by one. They start a new line at <m>\frac{2}{2}</m> and <m>\frac{4}{4}</m>, which are both whole numbers.)
      </li>
      <li><p>Consider asking:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><q>¿Quién puede describir el patrón con otras palabras?</q></li>
          <li><q>¿Alguien quiere compartir otra observación sobre por qué ocurre ese patrón aquí?</q></li>
          <li><q>¿Están de acuerdo o en desacuerdo? ¿Por qué?</q></li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>

</postlude>

</exploration>